content: SPOILER WARNING. This game is fantastic, but has continuity issues. In a playthrough I killed Carrie, only to have her briefly appear for some reason later when I met her father, then she was regarded as dead again later. In another playthrough I killed Harry. His brother Larry was owing me money after I demanded a stipend, and somehow later an occasional event I could choose had me collecting on money from dead man Harry instead of his brother. This issues are small but ruin the immersion.
Tons of fun and long
"Just stares at them"
Great!

Really emersive and well thought out/written story and the characters are fleshed out wonderfully, making your own cowpoke is fun and the choices are always entertaining. This is the standard that cyoa games should strive for. I still replay from time to time üß°ü§òü§ô
Very well written, not a railroad story like many other books out there. Absolutely love this
Amazing story, wish there was a little more!
Had a lot of fun but like most of these text based games i would like to have cheats available after beating the game like the archangel job. 5 stars
So damn good
This is how its done folks. Great story Amazing characters, and tons of detail.

This was fun! I was a Mandarin speaking, Doctor of Lawyers who ended up becoming a Marshall in the Wild West and becoming close friends with all the settlers and Native Americans alike. Now that was a crazy experience, if ever I had one!

I lost everything. I had gotten to the point of the river overflowing and having to protect the town. The levee I built broke and I chose "I could have sworn the levee would hold". Little did I know, this was the option to completely end the entire game and kill my character. Without warning, all the time I had put into the game was wasted and thrown away. The fact that something so unbelievably drastic and devastating can happen without a warning is nothing short of disgusting. Will uninstall.
I love playing a western
God-tier I loved the story and it even had replayability, which is rare for these kind of things. I encountered few bugs, which is also rare for this kind of thing.

Fantastic CYOA game, I have played alot of these games and this one has great depth. The choices really matter and the stats sheet plays a huge role. All in all ine of the best games I have played yet.

This game provides a well written story and very addicting. I kept playing it for hours and hours a day. I love it and look forward to Future games. The details in this story are amazing and you can have a good imagination of what is happening in the game.

The attention to detail in this cyoa is staggering. Captivating story, a multitude of storylines, and lots of options for replayability, over all money well spent! (I also appreciated the portrayals of the Mormons and the Native tribes in this story, where other stories so often misrepresent or flatten these groups, I respect the author's ability to showcase the dynamics, if only very breifly)
What a detailed and lasting experience. I cannot recommend this enough!

Look...I rarely ever leave reviews, but that is LITERALLY how fantastic this CYOA is. Where to start? The writing is clever, historically accurate, and truly engrosses you in this post-Civil War period of the Western frontier. The choices are very impactful and meaningful in the overall story, unlike many CYOA I have played. Above all, the characters populating this world are complex and well-written; on par with top RPGs. If you love becoming enveloped in great storytelling, PLAY THIS.
Great read. Fun, interesting and believable story and choices. One minor criticism is quite a few (minor) editing errors. But that's just the English major in me showing. Good game.
What a marvelous game! The story and characters really draw me in, and I really enjoy being able to develop my character in whatever direction I want!

Probably the best CYOA on the market. It's definitely the longest. Tons of scenarios, lots of options, great use of stats. This is how it's supposed to be done. Unfortunately, after playing this, most other CYOA are seriously lacking. It's made other CYOA games less fun. This is the new standard, and it's a tough one to best
I LOVED IT
Excellent
Enjoyed it
Wow. What a ride. If you like games like this or westerns in general and have the patience for a long choose your own adventure game this is one of the best ones I have played.
I've played through this game three times now. It's so, so good. I got completely immersed. Married Yiska three times.

Fantastic game, good deep RPG. Great world building and character choice. Great length too well worth the price. A game that had this much thought and effort is a steal at its current price. Buy this NOW.
It's an alright game

You guys make some of the best text based games Ive ever read. The stories, plots and characters are great. Engaged from beginning to end. I do have a request. Could you make a version that ran on flash or something like a website version, so I could access them from work whereas I cant have my phone or download things to the computer. That.would.be.amazing...
Absolutely loved this game

This is the best western choice of games I have played yet. A great deal of variety in each playthrough. You could kill everybody you meet or you can befriend everyone. This game is really adaptable to your play style. The plot is well done, the whole story tied together, every single character has a purpose and is fleshed out completely at the end of the story. With all the possible stats for this book there are many different ways to play. Western choice game. Highly recommend.
probably one of the best stories out there, if not the best, then the most amazing.
thought the game would be longer bit it was a really fun game. although i do have one question, SPOILERS, if marshal james was actually a ghost was your character actually a marshal?
When i play this game i think im done and don't want to play it anymore i end playing it the next day
one of my favorites out of all their games, truly a treasure!! I especially like the checkpoint system
amazing game and writing, really vivid imagery and immersed me in the story
Just what I wanted to read. The adventures are well written, well developed characters and plus the possibility of a polyamourous relationship. This is one of the best CoGs out there.
Great story and I loved it

what else can I say but this was simply masterclass with hardly any flaws and tbf non that I discovered, in the description it does not state how long the book is however I can assure you it is very long and well worth the money

In depth, detailed and fun. I enjoyed the story and characters. It does make ypu work to get the best outcomes, but nothing that can't be figured out with a little thought a logic. Wounderful premise, great writing and an all around good read. I have no real problems with the story that couldn't be chalked up to personal preference.
This is one of the best choice games I played. The choices do matter and the characters are written very well.
As far as choice books go this is my favourite, from story to stats everything was really satisfying
I just finished it and man oh man what a ride. From the start the game draws you in and doesn't let go. I loved the story, characters, and becoming a legend. Definitely worth picking up!

Worth the money. I took a gamble in paying straight away without the first chapter like in other hosted games I've played. Boy am i glad I did. Everything you want from a western. Intresting charecters, show downs, moral choices and more. One of the best things ive read or played.
By far the most involved of all of these games I've played. Excellent writing, good choice of gender and race, varied and interesting love interests, mystery, and history.

Easily the best story driven game ive ever played. hands down the amount of work and time that went into shows, and i cant be happier with the story telling itself. whoever wrote this should be working for a developer company. 10/10 would play again
Terrific game. Really enjoyed it. Great depth and detail to the story, and the choices you make really have an impact. A great example of interactive fiction
I thoroughly enjoyed the storyline and this author's work.

Tin Star boasts a rough, unforgiving setting and a spectacular amount of choice, featuring some of the most player freedom in the market. The attention to detail is exquisite, the usage of skills and stats is masterfully integrated with the story and choice system. And greatest of all is the utterly fluid plot structure, with a pacing that is completely natural. Sadly, holding Tin Star back from being a classic, are the relatively dry and simplistic characters, who lack the same level of nuance as the choices and plot surrounding them, though this isn't a mark against the writing, they are well written for what input the large cast of characters have.
An absolutely fantastic COG. Buy it now!
Incredible story

I am perplexed as to why I haven't rated this novel yet. It is one of the better hosted games' games it has quite a few different outcomes based on your choices not to mention how long the story feels and the detail it make me feel as though I'm in a real western. I love this novel.
Worth the money
great game ive playedit multiple times
very good CYOA game, well worth the price. would be nice if significant other could move in to homestead but oh well
One of the best so far. Great job to everyone who worked on this.
Fantastic

My God. This was certainly a trip, and not one that would soon be forgotten. When I play these games, it is usually ending in the same route, maybe a little change here ans there, depending on stats. This one though. This is a game that will spare no detail. The truest feeling of being a marshal in the old west was felt the whole way through. To remove characters at the beginning of the story or even later on. To end your story right there and start a new game. To make you feel like you belong in history amongst the greatest legends of all time. This game was an absolute pleasure to play. You have my thanks for all the hard work put into it.

The story amazing, choices matter, and all the characters matter
The New Vegas of text based RPGs. Tons of choices and every single choice has impact. Managed to be talking most folks down but had to shoot one guy in the leg and talk him down after.
An epic game made by epic people, never seen this much effort put in a text game before.
Changing all my Choice reviews from 5s to ones as you cannot reinstall after purchasing without rebuying their games. Own like 90% of them. Now hope they go under.
I loved all the different endings you could have. As well as the romance options. It's a shame there isn't a bigger fanbase with this since I'd love to see some fanart on the different characters.

This is easily the best CYOA story I've played. The writing got my attention with how the words and details made me feel like I was there and a part of it. The stats were done perfectly, I haven't seen a game with such a balanced and friendly approach towards "leveling up" your abilities. Thanks to all who helped create this game.

This game is great. But the number of times I've been kicked in the teeth 
by the checkpoint system and not been able to go to it freely is crazy. The 
only other issue with the game is that the evil mastermind at the end 
doesn't get a big enough part in the book. Apart from those two points this 
really is an enjoyable game.

Really good game! I like it, but it does get boring in some parts. Overall 
good though! It's long and aside from some boring parts it's entertaining :)

An absolute treat from start to finish. Masterwork writing and one hell of 
a story. If you haven't already bought and played this game, you're sorely 
missing out.

Bloody brilliant, long, in depth, and decisions that matter. That's before 
I even begin to describe the amazing world the story is set in. So many 
choices, it'll have you reading over and over again, which us just what you 
want from a good novel.
So involved and detailed, it amazes me.
I thought the whole gameplay and storytelling was amazing.
I love this game I could play through countless times

I did not like it. At all. After hearing so many great things about this one, I am deeply disappointed. The story has good length, but I could not feel connected to my MC and the characters - I only enjoyed the company one of them. Also, some parts are really boring to read - too many details. The author surely worked hard in this, and the price is fair. But for my tastes and expectations, it is sad to waste money in this.

I feel bad giving this less than 5 stars because there was clearly a lot of effort put into it. I spent a long time playing this, I got to chapter 6 before quitting.   There are a lot of detailed descriptions, but I feel like they are too detailed at times. For example, I don't need to read a detailed description of Hamlet while the character watches the play.   I also feel like the general premise of the story is a little unrealistic from the start as stated in a previous review.  I just didn't really feel pulled in or connected to the characters at chapter 6, so I decided to stop.   It looks like a lot of people enjoyed this, so you might enjoy it as well.   As I stated, there was definitely a lot of effort put into it.
Great story!

This is by far the greatest CYOA games. Our choices relly impacts the story and in the end they actually tell us the fates of the people we actually met and I repeated it lots of times and the ending was always different. enjoyed it while traveling
Best COG I've played, bar none. Had enough varied paths, secrets, and easter eggs to keep me occupied for months.
This was not only the hardest adventure ive read through but the most fun...make a sequil or something guys
Become a cowboy. Become a sheriff. Become a native. Become a lawyer while healing sick ppl at the mid of desert. 1 less star for the verbosity, tho. Not rly my taste.
Wow. I don't know how they accomplished paying attention to detail so much that really, I couldn't find any holes in the plot. One of the best ever interactive novels.
Endless adventure and romance
Great choice based game one of the best
Definitely better than the rest.Well written.
Absolutely love the story!!
One of the best Hosted Games has to offer. This is the story I base most of my reviews on, much to the detriment to many a game's scoring.
It was well worth the money.

Excellent writing, and plenty of variation The long Epilogue was a nice surprise as well. It's nice to know how my actions affected all the side-characters, though it made me feel a great deal of pity for my poor, neglected horse.

It's an interesting western story with a few memorable and fun characters. But it's ending is lackluster and has WAAAAY too many epilogues, It could have gone into more character interactions or development for the conspiracy. But it was still fun and has some replayability.
A little expensive for what it was its was pretty fun but it was kinda short and a little bland.
Loved it...
Good depth
Amazing Game, wish this writer released more games!
Out of all hosted game i've ever play, this one is the BEST, i really loved it and i really wish you guys would make another one like this!
This is by far my favourite novel ever. It has a long and compelling story that has tons of replayability. Link me to your paypal. I'd happily donate money to this guy.
I had fun being the marshal, with multiple choices that felt like actually affecting the end of the game.

The story is fairly well written and features an almost staggering attention to detail. The characters were a little bland and the romances could have been deeper. That being said the pay off at the end was a bit lackluster ( lots of build up, fairly tame send off) and I feel like I achieved the best ending on my first play through and so don't really have the motivation to play again. Overall, pretty good and deserves props for keeping me invested but not enough to want to replay

The game is excellent. The characters are well written and funny the plot is well conceived and while you do need to be a wild west enthusiast to understand EVERYTHING in this it is still fun. Like choice of robots it has excellent replay value with all the variations. The legend points in this were actually quite amusing like how my character stoped the sun shinning. The achievements are fun as well. I can now say there is a game were a war axe wielding Indian women rides a bear into battle.

The Marshall frames you for murder and pretends to hang you just to give you a job offer? And then threatens to kill you for real if you refuse? Why the hell would this inspire me to be a marshall for FOUR YEARS? Why the hell would I keep my word after leaving his crazy ass behind? This was so incredibly dumb, I refunded my payment. I've enjoyed all the Choice of games so far, but that was ridiculous.
I don't rate games often. I Have to rate this as Excellent. 10/10
The best choice of games work, hands down.
Best one yet

I've now played more than ten of these choose your own path games and I can say this is my second favorite one.  I feel like these games are all about the endings and this one addresses the different endings perfectly.  Well thought out and has replayability, which is a must for these types of games.
This author should definitely get invited to do a choice of.
So many choices that can change your outcome, and a good variety of love interests. I particularly like the epilogue that tells you the impact you make and the fate of the characters.
The best choice game out there, so many choices to make and you even get a homestead you can develop throughout the game. Some great characters and lots of side quests. Definitely recommend!
It took me a couple tries to get into this but once I did the story keep me intrigued the further I progressed.

Long, but quite linear. However each chapter has a variety of outcomes that affect how the  current populace and later history view you, as well how and if people are willing to help in later chapters. I enjoyed it enough to recommend. One of the best Hosted game I've played.
I honestly believe this is the best choice of games game available. The story is great. It is an unbelievable experience that you have to experience

Definitely the utmost pinnacle of interactive  fiction. I felt as if my choices had weight and genuinely regretted when things went wrong. If there are any better stories available in will be very surprised.
Very fun interactive novel.  Wish it was longer.

I am thoroughly impressed by the vast amount of choices and how they changed the story, it was all just perfect. Tin Star is so well accomplished as a whole: engrossing characters, thrilling story and seamless interactivity. That being said, it is hard to even imagine the effort and hours put into this game. Kudos!  Anyone who appreciates a high quality CYOA should get this gem - even if westerns aren't usually your cup of tea. Absolutely one of the best CYOAs I have played (on par with Choice of Robots).
It was great to experience the lawless wild west from a marshals perspective.
This is by far the best CoG...it completely draws you in...tons of replay value...
This made my watch go by soo much faster. Definitely an immersing story!
One of the best stories I have ever read and played through!
Long as hell, your choices have weight to them, a billion different paths, tons of romances, worth every cent. I'd happily pay $10 for this game.
Your allies matter,and so do your skills. Can you survive the terrors of the wild west only you can tell.
Great story! It was very long and engaging.
Great story! Worth every penny!
The best Choice of/Hosted game I've ever played. So much choice and a great plot line.
The most well-developed story contained in one CYOA game, hands down. I'm just sad that one of my two romances fell apart. :'(
Really nice story. Give you a feel of the old wide west.

Accurately 4.7/5 for me money well spent coming from me who has played many of these games and usually i dont spend money but i got worth more out of it. Its not 5/5 because i played this through a couple of parts and there seems to be some small glitches/misunderstandings in the story noticeably 2 i saw but it isn't to bad its still worth getting even if your skeptical getting your money's worth.

By far the longest and best CoG I've ever played (and I own 25 of them.) Exciting story with tons of options and fantastic replay value. I don't consider myself a fan of westerns, but this story nearly changed my mind.

Not usually a fan of westerns but this is out of this world, epic on scale and quality. I married Carrie and made her my deputy, and the legend rundown where it takes about her and said woe betide anyone who insulted the live of her life (me!) Actually made my heart flutter. Seriously don't hesitate get this now!
Well written, good amount of humor, great descriptions. It felt as though you were actually there. You learned of what happened to all the characters at the end which was cool. It is a must read.
it was fun to play this, very exciting. good job!

It took forever for me to finish, and everything was so beautiful. The characters, the options, the enemies and friends you could make. Do you wanna be a crooked sherriff or a brownnosing one, or maybe if you're one of them goodies you can be an honorable one and fix everything? Its all there and its all worth it.
Awesome. Tried to have a Clint Eastwood character built.
One of the best I have done
Probably the best one in the entire collection of this genre of games.

Played the end and loved every sentence of it. Has a good level of freedom of choice. Persuade, create a deal or just shoot to kill many of the criminals you'll met. There's also turns to improve skills and sides stories between the main story leading to the telling of your legend and showing how you affected other characters at the end which is a cool feature, also has a song(it's only lyrics but man it adds to the feel) better than just telling the epilouge and then THE END
Pay the price for it, it is worth it. There are many choices, the whole.saga is well written and it is very replayable.

This is by far the best Choice game ever. I am so happy I finally decided to buy it. The depth and scale of the story is vast. The writing and historic research book quality. Hours and hours of gameplay, with immense replay value. Buy this!
I love that there's so many different options and storylines.

Tin Star is a fantastic storybook game with a great many paths, a depth of character and choices that matter. Well written, well worth the purchase. Would love to see a sequel. If you enjoy other games by these folks, don't hesitate as it's right up there in the upper echelon.
Well, that was one heck of a ride. I enjoyed every second of it, even though it took me four tries to survive the bear XD. Highly recommended.
Loved the game, especially happy for being able to save even though it was the first game where I never really needed to reload :D
Great game,  too bad it's $2 more expensive on mobile. Must have been hard to port!
I love it.
I love it wish I could have at least 4 deputy's tho

Amazing story,  characters,  I played it over and over and over determined to see all the possible endings. One of my all time favorites. American stories usually bother me... I can't relate ... yet I could. At all times. Please write more stories- you are talented.
Many different outcomes, different characterization, and hidden path! So worth the money. Maximal replay ability.
This story hands down the best one CoG has offered. The depth of the story, the flow, everything just at the top level. I think it worth evey penny I spent on it
This game is pretty good but the story is too complex.

I love this app please make more story's in this world I would be happy to pay for them.
This game is worth its price.
I recommend you try Tin star

I'd put off playing this one, because I assumed it would glorify cowboys and white settlers, but whoever wrote this very clearly did their research about the times. This is one of the very very few choice of games that I replayed, and intend to replay again. It is long, developed, with different pathways and relationships to choose from. The writing is good, and left me feeling as any good book or movie should.
One of my favorite CoGs.  Memorable characters, great story, exellent dialouge, and heart pounding action. Just a thought could you make an ex slave character avaliable for the MC

Easily one of my favorites. Great story. I feel like my choices matter, and I can see a difference in choosing different things. The length of the story is perfect and it held my attention easily. I've played through the story at least 15 times, and it still doesn't bore me. To the devs, please keep updating. And Great work!!
Ive bought and played almost every one of these types of games I could find. This one is easily among the best. There is alot of detail and effort put into this one and your choices actually matter.

I have played these choice of games and other types of games like it and this is the best one so far. I was wary of the price but played the demo online and loved it, definitely didn't disappoint. Super long with amazing story progression. Money well spent. If you like this try sabres of infinity.
Tin Star is one of the longer Hosted games, and one of the most fleshed out. Each choice is a heavy one, and you really never know what will happen next.
This one's my favorite to date. Solidly done!
very deep and i love the romance

Worth the monies.
Great story. Hope to see more like it!
Despite some cliche moments while playing, I really enjoyed playing this game.
Best CoG/Hosted Game ever! I can't recommend this enough. Many choices to make, all of which result in widely different outcomes. Tin Star set an example to other CoG games.
Really good story and its quite long as well
I've played most of the cyoa games on the play store, and I have to say this one is the best.
Fantastic
I love this game
I really didn't like this.....

Took me a minute to not get my character to die, but it is one of the best hosted games has to offer. Very well written and not short at all. There are romance options and they aren't pushed on you.  Worth checking this one out.

It needs a better save system! I love this game and it is amazingly fun and I've already played though it twice but it really could use a better save system. I love the characters and the romances and if I had a better save system one I can access easily without dying I could do so much more! Without having to play the WHOLE GAME OVER. It is really a pain so please all I ask is a better save system otherwise this game is completely and utterly awesome and perfect

The quality of text adventures like this one really lives and dies by the quality of the writing and variety of choices; this game has an abundance of both.  I would recommend Tin Star to anybody who has even a passing interest in text adventure games.
5 stars. Long story, interesting several outcomes.

This was by far the best 5$ I've spent,  Ever. Seriously!  Great job dev. I can tell alot I of work went into this.  Definitely the longest "choice" game I've played so far. As soon as you finish, you'll want to go back and do it again. And again. And again.... The writing was great. The story was fantastic. Every choice you make genuinely feels like it has a major affect on something. Including other characters. Great romances, lots of endings. Perfect game! Worth 5$! Blessings
A fantastic cyoa. The characters are fully formed and the overall story is amazing. Your choices matter and define your legend.
I've purchased and played a lot of the hosted and choice of Games, this one is easily the best and is well worth the money
Really wasn't sure at first, but now I want to play over and over! Can't wait for more!

I enjoyed this one :) in not a big wild west fan but with the high rating I decided to give it a try.  I'm glad I did! Very interesting to read and kept me wanting to solve the issues and figure out problems.  My only complaint would be the use of the LDS people in the story.  For the most part I thought things were handled fine,  but there were a couple of parts that could have been left out.  I don't think it added to the story to have some of the religious things put out there like they were.

This one is a must-read. It's on a whole different level compared to even the 'official' CoG games. Your choices actually mattered. The writing is superb, and the storyline is epic. Other writers should take example from this one. Here's wishing for another release from the author. If the next release if as good as this, it'll be Insta-buy!
Good story

There are more choices than any choice of games non-hosted game I've ever played and leveling up certain things actually matters to the plot. You can die and there are checkpoints instead of starting all over. Choice of games should hire you guys!! Show them a thing or two. It was completely worth the money.
This is the first CoG I've bought on my phone and I was instantly hooked. Romances are pretty good and the story is great. I will definitely look into more of these games. Keep up the great work.
Really fun and addicting
Amazing.
Best game I have played in a  long time
One of the best. Really worth it. The story is long.
This game is brilliantly written, im hooked!
Easily one of the best by Hosted Games.

You could say I'm a pretty discerning cyoa-lover--Choice Of has been my go-to company since Choice of Romance was a new-release. I have played every one of their games to completion, save the two most recent sci-fi ones (this genre seems to fall flat for Choice Of), multiple times. I've also played nearly every single HOSTED game, save for ones that didn't appeal to me, a female (such as the Mariner, or whatever it's called, which is very male-oriented). Tin Star is easily the best.
I love this story. Every choice you make has an outcome. And love all the differentendings and paths to take. The story is long. The bedt I have readed.
By far one of the best games. out... kept me till the end hopin for a tin star 2
Already through my first year, and I'm hooked.  I'll bet there are a hundred ways of getting through the various challenges, and the characters are interesting and engaging.  Yiska is awesome!
Great plot line dont let the price scare you away
Simple yet elegant. Love it

Really enjoyed this, easily on a par with zombie exodus.  I only knocked off one star because there seem to be some strange jumps in the story at some point which I'm not sure if they are bugs or not.  Otherwise I'd highly recommend this!

Extremely well done story line with enthralling adventures and in depth characters and interactions. Worth the price with ten chapters of choosing your own story where every decision changes outcomes makes it worth replaying. If you liked this definitely check out Zombie Exodus and other Choice Of games.
Easily one of the best CoG games so far. If you like interactive fiction, this is a must-buy.
The best of the Choice Of games I've played so far. The writing is engaging, the characters three-dimensional, and the plot will keep you riveted.
It's in depth, has a compelling plot where every choice counts and amazing characters to boot. It's well worth the price if you enjoy Choice Of, or similar, games.
Interactive stories on your phone don't get better then this folks...
Definitely recommend
A bit too wordy but definitely worth the buy.  Very western based so some of the terms may be a bit foreign for those unfamiliar
This is the best text based game on the market! I hope to see more like this in the future
WELL WRITTEN AND AMAZING!!
what more can I say?! I really enjoyed the concept and I appreciate how much work has been put into making this one :-)
This is probably the best text based game ever. I love playing these games and a lot of times they are too short but this one is definitely worth buying.
